Description: Millennium Park is home to so many classics such as the Bean, rock climbing, water tower and concert hall!

Chapter: Maggie Daley Park Ice Skating Ribbon
Description: Who doesn't love some ice skating fun? Right in the center of Downtown Chicago is an ice rink that is open to the public during the winter. You must bring your own skates to enter!
Location: Maggie Daley Park Ice Skating Ribbon, Chicago

Description: Classic Chicago deep-dish pizza is served at Giordano's! This restaurant has been able to keep the tradition alive and does so deliciously!
Being such a diverse city, there is also diverse art. The Art Institute hosts thousands of art pieces from local artists and have their famous green lions in front!
Location: The Art Institute of Chicago, Chicago

Description: Creamy, smooth, silky homemade ice cream in a matter of minutes! This pop-shop has remained open for almost a century and the proof is in the ice cream!
Talk about an all-in-one stop for Chicago food classics! Hot dogs, sausage combos, crinkle cut fries, and delicious shakes is just the beginning of what Portillo's has to offer!
Taking a break from the busy streets and onto the calm waters; a river cruise takes you all around Chicago's famous buildings via boat!

Chapter: Gangsters and Ghosts Tour in Chicago
Description: The all famous gangsters and spooky hauntings are right here! Take a tour into life before we knew it!
Location: Gangsters and Ghosts Tour in Chicago
